# Literature Review: Intelligent Manufacturing Eco-system: A Post COVID-19 Recovery and Growth

Opportunity for Manufacturing Industry in Sub-Saharan Countries

## Introduction

The COVID-19 pandemic has disrupted various sectors, including the manufacturing industry, globally.
In Sub-Saharan countries, the manufacturing industry has faced severe challenges due to the pandemic.
However, it also presents an opportunity for recovery and growth through the adoption of intelligent
manufacturing practices. This literature review aims to explore the potential of intelligent manufacturing
as a post-COVID-19 recovery and growth opportunity for the manufacturing industry in Sub-Saharan
countries.

## Impact of COVID-19 on the Manufacturing Industry

The COVID-19 pandemic has had a significant impact on the manufacturing industry. Manufacturing
operations were disrupted due to lockdowns, travel restrictions, and supply chain interruptions. This led
to a decline in production, reduced demand, and financial losses for companies (Cai & Luo, 2020). The
manufacturing industry needs to adapt and find new ways to recover and grow in the post-pandemic era.

## Role of Intelligent Manufacturing in Post-COVID-19 Recovery

Intelligent manufacturing, also known as Industry 4.0 or smart manufacturing, involves the integration of
advanced technologies, such as robotics, artificial intelligence, and the Internet of Things, to enhance manufacturing processes and productivity (Rahman et al., 2021). The adoption of intelligent manufacturing
practices can provide several benefits to the manufacturing industry in Sub-Saharan countries, enabling
them to recover and grow in the post-COVID-19 era.

## Service Robots in the Healthcare Sector

The COVID-19 pandemic has accelerated the development and adoption of service robots in the healthcare
sector. Service robots have been utilized to overcome the difficulties and hardships caused by the virus,
including reducing human-to-human contact and providing assistance in hospitals and healthcare facilities
(Shen et al., 2021). The integration of service robots in the manufacturing industry can play a crucial role
in ensuring the safety and efficiency of production processes.

## Readiness of Italian Regions for Industry 4.0

A study conducted in Italy assessed the readiness and responsiveness of Italian regions in adopting
Industry 4.0 practices to accelerate sustainable manufacturing in the COVID-19 era. The findings revealed
