## Conclusion

Intelligent manufacturing presents a promising opportunity for the manufacturing industry in Sub-Saharan
countries to recover and grow in the post-COVID-19 era. By integrating advanced technologies and
practices, such as robotics, artificial intelligence, and the Internet of Things, Sub-Saharan countries can
enhance their manufacturing processes, improve productivity, and compete in the global market. However,
further research is needed to address the knowledge gaps and understand the specific challenges and
opportunities faced by Sub-Saharan countries in adopting intelligent manufacturing practices. This will
enable policymakers and industry stakeholders to develop targeted strategies and interventions to leverage
the potential of intelligent manufacturing for post-pandemic recovery and growth.

